                        To go to page click
                        <em><b><u><a href="/Report/TestReport">Report 2</a></b></u></em>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo">
                        2. Products
                    </a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <div id="modifyawards">
                        Modify Awards
                        <p>From the PRODUCTS tab, this page allows you to create a new product or search for an existing product from the search bar. The table shown will list all currently available products by their Product Name, Price, Category Name, and Status. </p>
                        <p>
                            To go to page click
                            <em><b><u><a href="/Product">Modify Awards</a></b></u></em>
                        </p>

                        <div id="prodcategory"> Add Product Category </div>
                        <p>From the PRODUCTS tab, this page allows you to create a new category of products for which they will be classified by. The table lists all added categories by their Category Name and Status.</p>
                        <p>
                            To go to page click
                            <em><b><u><a href="/Category">Add Product Category</a></b></u></em>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree">
                        3. Activites
                    </a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <div id="viewcompleted"> View Completed Activities </div>
                    <p>From the ACTIVITIES tab, this page allows you to add a completed student activity by clicking “Add New”. You will then be directed to the New Activity Transaction page. From there, you will select a User Profile, an Activity Date and an Activity and click Create or you can select Back to Completed Activities. The table lists all completed activities by Student Name, Activity Date, Activity Name, Points Earned, and an option to modify the completed activity. </p>
                    <p>
                        To go to page click
                        <em><b><u><a href="/ActivityTransaction">View Completed Activities</a></b></u></em>
                    </p>

                    <div id="inputcompleted"> Input Completed Activity </div>
                    <p>From the ACTIVITIES tab, this page will allow you to create a new activity transaction by selecting the user from a drop down, the date, and the activity from a drop down menu. </p>
                    <p>
                        To go to page click
                        <em><b><u><a href="/ActivityTransaction/Create">Input Completed Activity</a></b></u></em>
                    </p>

                    <div id="addreward"> Add Reward Activity </div>
                    <p>From the ACTIVITIES tab, this page will display a table detailing all currently eligible activities by Activity Name, Description, and Point Value. You can click Add Activity to add a new one to the table. You would then input the Activity Name, Description, and Point Value and select Create. These activities will then be available for teachers to select when a student has completed an activity from the list.  </p>
                    <p>
                        To go to page click
                        <em><b><u><a href="/ActivityTransaction/Activity">Add Reward Activity</a></b></u></em>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFour">
                        4. ToolBox
                    </a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <div id="viewacct"> View Student Accounts </div>
                    <p>
                        From the TOOLBOX tab, this page will display a table showing each participating student by: Student Name, First Name, Last Name, Email Address, Point Total, and School Name.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        To go to page click
                        <em><u><b><a href="/User">View Student Accounts</a></b></u></em>
                    </p>

                    <div id="editroles"> Edit User Roles </div>
                    <p>From the TOOLBOX tab,this page will allow you to select: Edit Roles, Create New Roles, or Go Home. By clicking Edit Roles, you will be directed to a table displaying all users by: User ID, Username, and a checked-box according to their user-type. By clicking Create New Roles you can type in a new role to add and click the Add button. -If you click Home it sends you to the Home Page.</p>
                    <p>
                        To go to page click
                        <em><u><b><a href="/Roles">Edit User Roles</a></b></u></em>
                    </p>

                    <div id="add/removeschools"> Add/Remove Schools </div>
                    <p>From the TOOLBOX tab, you have the option of adding and removing schools. In order to Add a school to the system, you will select Create New. You will then be directed to a set of fields where you can enter a School Name, Address, City, State, Zip Code, and Phone Number. After selecting create the new school will be added to the table.  </p>
                    <p>
                        To go to page click
                        <em><u><b><a href="/School">Add/Remove Schools</a></b></u></em>
                    </p>

                    <div id="editfrpage"> Edit Front Page Text </div>
                    <p>From the TOOLBOX tab, you will have the option to edit the contents of the Home Page. Perhaps you want to display an upcoming community service event or tennis tryouts; this would be the area to do so. The initial page displays the current text and if you click Edit Front Page Text, you will be directed to fields in which you can modify. These fields are denoted by the area in which the text will appear on the page.  </p>
                    <p>
                        To go to page click
                        <em><u><b><a href="/FrontPage">Edit Front Page Text</a></b></u></em>
                    </p>

                    <div id="adminpanel"> Admin Panel </div>
                    <p>Don’t have a damn clue what this does…..Mark???! Do you know? </p>
                    <p>
                        To go to page click
                        <em><u><b><a href="/FrontPage">Admin Panel</a></b></u></em>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

